                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13663456" author="enis" created="Tue, 21 May 2013 21:52:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test itself can check the cluster size, and whether in distributed mode and decide to not run, or run with success. Is this good enough, or you are talking about having a different category? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13663721" author="sershe" created="Wed, 22 May 2013 03:22:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;some tests don&apos;t make sense on mini cluster because they test scenarios for large perf... it&apos;s both useless to run them with small numbers, and it&apos;s also good to be able to set config to large by default for common case&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13664355" author="enis" created="Wed, 22 May 2013 18:06:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree with that statement, I am just trying to understand whether you are proposing a new category or we can do this per test. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13664372" author="sershe" created="Wed, 22 May 2013 18:19:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For ITD, we could get away with additional attribute per test that it can use.&lt;br/&gt;
I am not sure about maven... may need a new category.&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe we can make tests that never run in maven, so you can only run them in cluster using ITD.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13664396" author="jmhsieh" created="Wed, 22 May 2013 18:33:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Would it make sense to have a separate module for perf and scale only integration tests?  hbase-it-perf?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13664619" author="enis" created="Wed, 22 May 2013 22:28:55 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Would it make sense to have a separate module for perf and scale only integration tests? hbase-it-perf?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Over at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7840&quot; title=&quot;Enhance the java it framework to start &amp;amp; stop a distributed hbase &amp;amp; hadoop cluster &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7840&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7840&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Nicolas is building a framework for MTTR tests using and enhancing CM. I proposed there that we can have a mttr/perf category of benchmark tests since it does not make sense to run them as regular tests, but being able to run them and inspect the results. A perf module in this case makes sense. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13786835" author="sershe" created="Sat, 5 Oct 2013 01:13:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;place for such tests is probably just perf benchmakr&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
